Screenshot (console command)
============================

Description
-----------

This command takes a snapshot of the current screen and saves it to file.

Usage
-----

At the console type...

`screenshot [Width] [Height] [Samples]`

Parameters
----------

All the parameters are optional.

-   [Width] - Screen size in pixels.
-   [Height] - Screen size in pixels.
-   [Samples] - Number of shots taken.

Notes
-----

This command will generate a .[TGA](TGA\_(file\_format)). The [Antialiasing](Samples] value will provide artificial [Antialiasing) by blending all the shots together. If you'd like to simulate soft shadows in a Doom 3 screenshot you can set the following in your [autoexec.cfg](CFG\_(file\_format)):

`bind F11 "[R_useOptimizedShadows_(cvar).html r_useOptimizedShadows] 0;[R_lightSourceRadius_(cvar).html r_lightSourceRadius] 5;screenshot 1024 768 64"`


